quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  6,51,"And warn through the (Quran) those who fear that they will be gathered towards their Fosterer, there will be no guardian for them besides Him and there will be no mediator, that they may guard (themselves against evil)"
  6,52,"And do not drive away those who pray to their Fosterer in the morning and the evening intending (to seek) His Attention, you are not accountable for them in anything and they are not accountable for you in anything, so that (by) your driving them away you become (one) of the unjust"
  6,53,"And thus do We test some of them through others, so that they say, \"Are these the persons upon whom Allah has showered His favour from among us?\" Is not Allah the Best Knower of those who are grateful"
  6,54,"And when those who believe in Our signs come to you, then say (to them), \"Peace be on you, your Fosterer has prescribed mercy on Himself, so if anyone of you did evil in ignorance then repented after that and amended, then He is certainly Protectively Forgiving, Merciful"
  6,55,And thus do We explain the signs that the way of the criminals may become clear